quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  17,1,"Highly Exalted is the One Who took His servant on a journey by night from the Inviolable Mosque1to the Farthest Mosque2, whose precincts Wea have blessed, in order to show him of Our signs; indeed, He is the All-Hearing, the All-Seeing."
  17,2,"And We brought Moses the Scripture and made it guidance for the Children of Israel: “Take1 none for trustee other than Me,"
  17,3,"(O) offspring of those We carried with Noah; indeed, he was a constantly thankful servant.”"
  17,4,"And We decreed for the Children of Israel in the Scripture: “You will most surely corrupt in the land twice, and you will most surely rise to a great height."
  17,5,"Then when the promise of the first of the two times came true, We sent against youpl servants of Ours possessing intense force, and they ransacked the homes, and it was a promise fulfilled.”"
  17,6,"Then We gave youpl back your turn against them and supplied you with wealth and offspring and made you more numerous."
  17,7,"If you excel in doing good, you excel in doing good to your own benefit; and if you do evil, you do so against yourselves. Then when the promise of the second time comes true, they1 will defileyour faces, and they will enter the Mosque as they entered it the first time, and they will utterly destroy all that falls into their power."